# Per-repo gitleaks fingerprint allowlist.
#
# Each line is a "fingerprint" (path:rule-id:secret-line-hash) that
# gitleaks prints when it reports a finding. Add a fingerprint here
# only if you've manually verified that the hit is a false positive
# (e.g. a documented demo value that the path/regex allowlist in
# .gitleaks.toml didn't catch).
#
# Format:
#   <fingerprint>           # one per line, comments with # OK
#
# Example:
#   docs/example.md:hex-private-key-bare:abcd1234
#
# Maintained by: whoever pushed the repo. Review by: Henrik (audit).

